President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has signed the "COVID-19 Origin Act of 2023" into law, expressing his commitment to releasing as much information as possible regarding the origin of COVID-19. The President had previously directed the Intelligence Community to thoroughly investigate the origins of the virus, with the aim of preventing future pandemics. The Administration will continue to review classified information, including potential links to the Wuhan Institute of Virology, and will declassify and share as much of that information as possible, while ensuring national security is not compromised. The statement was released on March 20, 2023.